---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import SEOHead from '../components/SEOHead.astro';
import { url } from '../utils/paths';
---
<Base title="Services" description="AI agent teams, automated content production, image enhancement, and SEO — Manual Focus puts AI to work inside your marketing operation.">
  <SEOHead slot="seo" type="website" title="Services" description="AI agent teams, automated content production, image enhancement, and SEO — Manual Focus puts AI to work inside your marketing operation." />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>What we build for you</h1>
      <p class="lead">We install AI systems inside your marketing operation. Agent teams that produce content, optimise your site, enhance your images, and report back with results. You keep your existing team focused on the work that needs a human brain.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail">
        <h2>AI agent teams</h2>
        <p class="service-for">For marketing teams drowning in repetitive work that never seems to end.</p>
        <p>We design, build, and deploy teams of AI agents that handle the operational load your team shouldn't be carrying. Content drafting, competitor monitoring, data reporting, social scheduling, email sequences — we configure agents for each job, connect them to your tools, and get them running.</p>
        <h3>What this looks like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Custom agent teams built around your specific workflows</li>
          <li>Agents connected to your CMS, analytics, CRM, and ad platforms</li>
          <li>Automated content drafting, review pipelines, and publishing</li>
          <li>Competitive intelligence agents that surface opportunities daily</li>
          <li>Reporting agents that pull, summarise, and distribute performance data</li>
          <li>Ongoing tuning as your operation evolves</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>What this is not</h3>
        <p>We don't sell chatbots or bolt a GPT wrapper onto your website. These are purpose-built agents that do real work inside your existing stack.</p>
        <a href={url('/enquire')} class="btn-cta" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Enquire about AI agent teams</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail">
        <h2>Automated product creation</h2>
        <p class="service-for">For e-commerce and product businesses that need to scale content without scaling headcount.</p>
        <p>We build pipelines that turn raw product data — specs, features, images — into publish-ready listings, descriptions, and campaign copy. New SKU? The pipeline handles it. Seasonal refresh? Batch it and go. No writer bottleneck, no freelancer delays.</p>
        <h3>What this looks like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Automated product description generation from specs and data sheets</li>
          <li>Multi-channel copy — your website, marketplaces, ads, email — from one source</li>
          <li>Brand voice calibration so output sounds like your team wrote it</li>
          <li>Batch processing for catalogue updates and seasonal launches</li>
          <li>Human review workflows where you want a final check</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>What this is not</h3>
        <p>We don't produce generic AI slop. Every pipeline is calibrated to your brand, your audience, and your tone. If it reads like a robot wrote it, we haven't finished.</p>
        <a href={url('/enquire')} class="btn-cta" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Enquire about automated production</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail">
        <h2>Image enhancement</h2>
        <p class="service-for">For teams that spend too much time on image editing, resizing, and asset prep.</p>
        <p>One product photo in, twenty platform-ready variants out. We set up AI-powered image pipelines that handle background removal, resizing, colour correction, format conversion, and optimisation — so your team stops pushing pixels and starts shipping.</p>
        <h3>What this looks like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Bulk background removal and replacement</li>
          <li>Automatic resizing and cropping for every platform and ad spec</li>
          <li>AI upscaling and quality enhancement for low-res source images</li>
          <li>Consistent colour grading across product catalogues</li>
          <li>Web-optimised output that keeps your page speed fast</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>What this is not</h3>
        <p>This doesn't replace creative direction. You still decide what looks right. We just remove the manual labour between the brief and the final asset.</p>
        <a href={url('/enquire')} class="btn-cta" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Enquire about image enhancement</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-detail">
        <h2>SEO audit and boost</h2>
        <p class="service-for">For businesses that know their SEO needs work but don't have the bandwidth to fix it.</p>
        <p>We run a full AI-driven audit of your site — technical health, content quality, internal linking, schema markup, page speed, and competitor positioning. Then we fix what's broken and set up monitoring agents that keep things healthy week over week. Not a PDF of recommendations. Actual fixes.</p>
        <h3>What this looks like</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Full technical SEO audit with prioritised fix list</li>
          <li>Content gap analysis — what your competitors rank for and you don't</li>
          <li>AEO (Answer Engine Optimisation) for LLM and AI search visibility</li>
          <li>Schema markup, meta data, and internal linking improvements</li>
          <li>Ongoing monitoring agents that flag regressions and new opportunities</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>What this is not</h3>
        <p>We don't do keyword stuffing or grey-hat tricks. We build the kind of SEO foundation that keeps working as search engines get smarter, not the kind that breaks the next time Google ships an update.</p>
        <a href={url('/enquire')} class="btn-cta" style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">Enquire about SEO</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .lead {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: var(--max-width);
  }

  .service-detail {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
  }

  .service-for {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .service-detail h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  }

  .service-detail ul {
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .service-detail ul li {
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .service-detail > p {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .section-alt {
    background-color: rgba(29, 29, 27, 0.02);
  }
</style>
